            "answer_text": "The underlying assumption is that cryptographic methods depends only on the factorisation of large numbers. That is not true. There are other cryptographic methods such as rhe one shown below: Hidden subgroup problem - Wikipedia Shor's algorithm essential transforms the prime factorisation problem to a problem related to some operations on Abelian (commutative) groups. The hidden subgroup problem cannot be solved by the approach Shor's algorithm uses so is still unsolvable by that method. This is just about what my limited knowledge is which I acquired from the Quantum Computing course by Prof. Apoorva Patel I am taking this semester. ",
